{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:sirach.34",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 34,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 34 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:1",
      "text": "The hopes of a man void of understanding are vain and false: and dreams lift up fools.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:2",
      "text": "Whoso regardeth dreams is like him that catcheth at a shadow, and followeth after the wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:3",
      "text": "The vision of dreams is the resemblance of one thing to another, even as the likeness of a face to a face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:4",
      "text": "Of an unclean thing what can be cleansed? and from that thing which is false what truth can come?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:5",
      "text": "Divinations, and soothsayings, and dreams, are vain: and the heart fancieth, as a woman’s heart in travail.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:6",
      "text": "If they be not sent from the most High in thy visitation, set not thy heart upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:7",
      "text": "For dreams have deceived many, and they have failed that put their trust in them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:8",
      "text": "The law shall be found perfect without lies: and wisdom is perfection to a faithful mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:9",
      "text": "A man that hath travelled knoweth many things; and he that hath much experience will declare wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:10",
      "text": "He that hath no experience knoweth little: but he that hath travelled is full of prudence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:11",
      "text": "When I travelled, I saw many things; and I understand more than I can express.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:12",
      "text": "I was ofttimes in danger of death: yet I was delivered because of these things.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:13",
      "text": "The spirit of those that fear the Lord shall live; for their hope is in him that saveth them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:14",
      "text": "Whoso feareth the Lord shall not fear nor be afraid; for he is his hope.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:15",
      "text": "Blessed is the soul of him that feareth the Lord: to whom doth he look? and who is his strength?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:16",
      "text": "For the eyes of the Lord are upon them that love him, he is their mighty protection and strong stay, a defence from heat, and a cover from the sun at noon, a preservation from stumbling, and an help from falling.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:17",
      "text": "He raiseth up the soul, and lighteneth the eyes: he giveth health, life, and blessing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:18",
      "text": "He that sacrificeth of a thing wrongfully gotten, his offering is ridiculous; and the gifts of unjust men are not accepted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:19",
      "text": "The most High is not pleased with the offerings of the wicked; neither is he pacified for sin by the multitude of sacrifices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:20",
      "text": "Whoso bringeth an offering of the goods of the poor doeth as one that killeth the son before his father’s eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:21",
      "text": "The bread of the needy is their life: he that defraudeth him thereof is a man of blood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:22",
      "text": "He that taketh away his neighbour’s living slayeth him; and he that defraudeth the labourer of his hire is a bloodshedder.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:23",
      "text": "When one buildeth, and another pulleth down, what profit have they then but labour?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:24",
      "text": "When one prayeth, and another curseth, whose voice will the Lord hear?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:25",
      "text": "He that washeth himself after the touching of a dead body, if he touch it again, what availeth his washing?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:sirach.34.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 34,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 34:26",
      "text": "So is it with a man that fasteth for his sins, and goeth again, and doeth the same: who will hear his prayer? or what doth his humbling profit him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
